WEBVTT

00:01.210 --> 00:03.045
PILAR:
Last season on Love, Victor...

00:03.045 --> 00:04.505
VICTOR:
Mom, Dad.

00:04.505 --> 00:05.547
I'm gay,

00:05.547 --> 00:07.341
and I'm with Benji now.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.884
I don't want it to be a secret anymore.

00:08.884 --> 00:10.093
- When did you decide this?

00:10.093 --> 00:12.888
VICTOR:
I didn't decide it. I just am it.

00:12.888 --> 00:14.139
Benji's my boyfriend,

00:14.139 --> 00:16.265
and I'd like you to call him that.

00:16.265 --> 00:18.393
Some guys on my team
don't want me changing.

00:19.603 --> 00:21.813
- You should be around people
who want you to be you.

00:21.813 --> 00:23.774
- Say the word,
and I will ditch these gays

00:23.774 --> 00:25.734
like a corporation after Pride Month.

00:25.734 --> 00:28.487
- Wait, are you and Felix
gonna do it this weekend?

00:28.487 --> 00:30.822
- So on three,
we're gonna drop our towels.

00:30.822 --> 00:32.115
- Benji's had sex before,

00:32.115 --> 00:33.992
and I have no idea what I'm doing.

00:33.992 --> 00:36.495
- Mia, I've waited pretty
much my entire life

00:36.495 --> 00:38.497
to be exactly where I am right now.

00:38.497 --> 00:41.208
- Last night was...
- Yeah, it was.

00:41.208 --> 00:43.001
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

00:43.001 --> 00:45.379
ISABEL:
What excuse could you possibly have

00:45.379 --> 00:46.839
for doing that in my house?

00:46.839 --> 00:48.006
- Sex or gay sex?

00:48.507 --> 00:50.759
FELIX:
She's been depressed for a while now.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.302
She barely gets out of bed.

00:52.302 --> 00:53.929
- I think we need to get you some help.

00:53.929 --> 00:54.888
- No.

00:54.888 --> 00:57.558
- He asked you not to say
anything about his mom and now

00:57.558 --> 00:59.309
she's being detained.

00:59.309 --> 01:00.686
- Wait, wait, you're sober?

01:00.686 --> 01:01.812
We tell each other everything.

01:01.812 --> 01:03.939
- I've put up with a ton of your shit.

01:03.939 --> 01:05.649
♪

01:05.649 --> 01:08.944
RAHIM:
Dear Victor. My name is Rahim. I'm gay.

01:08.944 --> 01:10.320
- You're a catch, Rahim.

01:10.320 --> 01:13.490
- Someone has a little crush.
- On Felix? Yeah, right.

01:13.490 --> 01:15.450
FELIX:
Last night was, like, more fun

01:15.450 --> 01:17.369
than I had in, like, forever.

01:17.369 --> 01:19.955
- I can't just pretend that
everything between us is normal

01:19.955 --> 01:21.206
after I kissed you.

01:21.206 --> 01:22.332
FELIX:
Lake and I broke up.

01:22.332 --> 01:23.792
♪

01:23.792 --> 01:27.004
- I'm not giving up on God.
I'm giving up on you.

01:27.462 --> 01:30.924
Thank you for being so patient with me.

01:30.924 --> 01:33.343
- The president of Stamford is retiring,

01:33.343 --> 01:35.095
and he offered me the job.

01:35.095 --> 01:37.097
ANDREW:
Ripping her away from her home.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.724
I don't think she'll ever
come back from that.

01:38.724 --> 01:40.559
MIA:
Let's go see my mom.

01:40.559 --> 01:42.895
- I never really saw you with him anyway.

01:42.895 --> 01:44.021
- Who'd you see me with?

01:44.021 --> 01:45.856
- Someone totally different.

01:45.856 --> 01:47.858
♪ I know that it's hard sometimes ♪

01:47.858 --> 01:50.652
RAHIM: I swear I never meant
to get in between you and Benji.

01:50.652 --> 01:51.820
- I feel like such an idiot.

01:51.820 --> 01:52.988
- I'm not allowed to have a friend?

01:52.988 --> 01:54.489
- I don't think that's all this is.

01:54.489 --> 01:57.451
- Now, imagine all the future things
you wanna do with your boyfriend.

01:57.451 --> 01:58.994
Who do you see?

01:58.994 --> 02:01.163
♪ We'll be making sense of this ♪

02:01.163 --> 02:04.166
♪ Together, we can work it out ♪

02:05.250 --> 02:06.001
- Hi.

02:06.001 --> 02:07.878
♪ This could be the end of it ♪

02:09.671 --> 02:11.590
[door creaks open]

02:13.717 --> 02:15.636
- Hi.

02:16.970 --> 02:18.180
- Hi.

02:18.180 --> 02:21.558
- I-I couldn't let the night end
with you thinking that I moved on.

02:21.558 --> 02:23.894
- Victor, I, uh...

02:23.894 --> 02:25.896
- Did I ever tell you

02:25.896 --> 02:28.106
about the first time that I saw you?

02:29.191 --> 02:30.442
It was my first day at Creekwood,

02:30.442 --> 02:33.070
and you were at the water fountain,

02:33.070 --> 02:35.322
uh, by the teacher's lounge,

02:35.322 --> 02:36.406
looking insanely cool.

02:36.406 --> 02:37.407
♪

02:37.407 --> 02:39.159
And at that moment, I realized

02:39.159 --> 02:42.079
this lie that I've been telling myself
for my whole life just...

02:44.081 --> 02:45.332
went up in smoke.

02:46.458 --> 02:48.335
You changed my life.

02:49.127 --> 02:51.129
I love you, Benji.

02:51.797 --> 02:53.674
It's always been you.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.886
- I love you, too.

03:00.347 --> 03:01.640
CHARLES:
Good god, man.

03:01.640 --> 03:02.850
Benji's mom is always on me

03:02.850 --> 03:04.351
about being more romantic.

03:04.351 --> 03:05.853
I should take lessons from you, Victor.

03:05.853 --> 03:07.855
[laughs]
- Dad, can you get out of here?

03:08.856 --> 03:12.192
- Actually, maybe we can get out of here.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.236
There's, uh, somewhere I wanna take you.

03:14.236 --> 03:16.738
But, you would have to drive.

03:16.738 --> 03:18.365
I-I kind of ran here.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.577
- And he ran here? Go. Have fun.
Take my car.

03:22.286 --> 03:23.537
But not too much fun.

03:23.537 --> 03:25.664
Don't have sex in my car.
I just got it detailed.

03:25.664 --> 03:28.667
♪ "Electric Indigo"
by The Paper Kites playing ♪

03:39.219 --> 03:42.639
- You know, when you said
you were taking me somewhere romantic,

03:42.639 --> 03:44.641
I wasn't really picturing school.

03:45.309 --> 03:48.103
- Yeah, but where exactly
at school are we?

03:48.937 --> 03:51.190
♪ Never meant to
cause you trouble ♪

03:51.190 --> 03:53.817
BENJI: The bench where
we had our first real kiss.

03:54.860 --> 03:56.361
Spring Fling.

03:58.906 --> 04:01.408
♪ But you holding me
with something ♪

04:01.408 --> 04:03.911
♪ Locked behind your eyes ♪

04:11.335 --> 04:12.586
- Can we just...

04:13.504 --> 04:15.005
go back to that perfect moment?

04:16.798 --> 04:18.467
You know, start over?

04:19.760 --> 04:22.095
- Are you sure nothing's
going on with you and Rahim?

04:24.598 --> 04:26.183
- Rahim...

04:26.183 --> 04:27.434
kissed me at the wedding.

04:29.561 --> 04:31.271
And I didn't stop him.

04:31.271 --> 04:33.482
I thought we were friends, and...

04:34.191 --> 04:36.985
things got confused,
but I-I'm not confused now.

04:38.737 --> 04:39.780
I swear.

04:41.198 --> 04:43.075
- Is he a good kisser?

04:43.867 --> 04:46.828
- I feel like I should say no,
so I'm just going to go with no.

04:46.828 --> 04:48.080
[both laugh]

04:51.750 --> 04:53.168
Benji, I'm sorry.

04:54.837 --> 04:57.840
♪

04:59.132 --> 05:00.634
- I'm sorry...

05:01.468 --> 05:05.013
for being such a jerk about your mom.

05:06.640 --> 05:09.852
I... I just-- I hated seeing you get hurt
over and over again,

05:09.852 --> 05:12.437
a-and I wanted to protect you. I just...

05:12.437 --> 05:13.939
didn't know how.

05:14.815 --> 05:16.483
So, I lashed out.

05:19.862 --> 05:21.864
- I'm sorry I didn't fight for us sooner.

05:24.867 --> 05:27.870
I wish we could've just...
talked like this before.

05:29.997 --> 05:32.749
- We wasted so much time.

05:34.001 --> 05:37.045
♪

05:47.431 --> 05:50.100
♪ Somebody to tell me it'll be alright ♪

05:50.100 --> 05:53.061
♪ Somebody to tell me it'll be just fine ♪

05:53.061 --> 05:55.063
♪ If someone has been there before ♪

05:55.063 --> 05:58.442
♪ Say right now,
'cause I just need to hear it ♪

06:03.739 --> 06:05.574
♪

06:05.574 --> 06:08.285
- That's the third time
you've looked out that window tonight.

06:08.285 --> 06:11.371
- Just admiring the window dressings.

06:11.371 --> 06:12.497
Is this raffia?

06:12.497 --> 06:14.833
- You know they are. You picked them out.

06:16.084 --> 06:17.586
Who are you waiting for?

06:18.921 --> 06:21.423
- I thought someone might show up.

06:22.799 --> 06:24.134
Now, I'm not so sure.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.678
- Is this someone a boy?

06:29.181 --> 06:30.599
Why don't you pray?

06:30.599 --> 06:32.601
- That's your answer for everything.

06:32.601 --> 06:35.771
- Or you could look out the window again.
That seems to be working.

06:35.771 --> 06:37.773
- Good night, Maman.

06:40.150 --> 06:41.443
- That's four times.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.739
♪

06:46.532 --> 06:48.116
- Mm! Fun fact.

06:48.116 --> 06:51.370
Did you know your tongue print is
as unique as your fingerprint?

06:51.370 --> 06:53.997
So, you know, you shouldn't go
committing crimes with your tongue.

06:53.997 --> 06:56.041
- How about less fun facts, more kissing?

06:58.877 --> 07:00.295
[knocking]

07:03.715 --> 07:06.093
- Hi, Pilar.
- Felix is waiting for Victor

07:06.093 --> 07:08.136
to get back from the wedding.
That's why he's here.

07:08.136 --> 07:10.347
- Okay. Uh, hey, Felix.

07:11.139 --> 07:13.767
So, we have a little news...
BOTH: You're back together!

07:13.767 --> 07:16.311
- What? How did you--
- It was either that or divorce,

07:16.311 --> 07:19.314
and it'd be really weird to announce
a divorce while holding hands.

07:20.566 --> 07:22.401
♪

07:22.401 --> 07:23.694
ARMANDO: Look at that.
[both giggle]

07:23.694 --> 07:27.155
Yes. Uh, your mother and I,
we really want to make it work.

07:27.155 --> 07:28.657
- I'm sure you have a lot of questions.

07:28.657 --> 07:32.494
- Nope. No questions. I'm happy.
Good job. Congratulations.

07:33.161 --> 07:35.414
- Guys, just bring it in here!

07:35.414 --> 07:36.874
[laughing]
Oh man.

07:36.874 --> 07:38.876
Gosh, I love love.

07:38.876 --> 07:41.044
Oh! And, you know, speaking of love--

07:41.044 --> 07:43.589
- Ah! [laughs] Oh gosh.

07:43.589 --> 07:46.425
It took a second for the emotions
to hit me, but, wow,

07:46.425 --> 07:48.177
we really are a family again.

07:48.177 --> 07:49.303
- Thank you, cariño. Look,

07:49.303 --> 07:51.221
we just want you to know
that we love you so much.

07:51.221 --> 07:54.016
Same, same, same. Go Salazars!
ISABEL: Yay!

07:54.016 --> 07:57.019
- ¡Felicidades!
ISABEL: Oh. If you're hungry, just--

07:59.479 --> 08:02.858
- So, from the way you flung me
clear across the room,

08:02.858 --> 08:05.277
I'm getting that
you don't want them to know.

08:06.612 --> 08:08.030
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

08:08.030 --> 08:11.867
It's just that we've been
together for, like, 10 seconds.

08:11.867 --> 08:14.203
I just want to enjoy the fun
fooling around thing

08:14.203 --> 08:16.788
a little bit longer before we
start telling people about us.

08:16.788 --> 08:18.290
Okay?

08:20.083 --> 08:23.128
- I guess our unique tongue prints
do have some acquainting to do.

08:23.128 --> 08:26.048
[party chatter]
[music playing]

08:26.715 --> 08:28.842
MIA:
Well, this is the address in the emails.

08:28.842 --> 08:30.427
- It's not too late to turn around.

08:31.386 --> 08:32.638
- Nope.

08:32.638 --> 08:35.265
- I, uh, haven't seen
my mom in five years.

08:36.099 --> 08:38.227
I want some answers.

08:39.269 --> 08:40.979
- Then let's get you some answers.

08:40.979 --> 08:43.273
♪

08:43.273 --> 08:45.651
I also really have to pee.

08:45.651 --> 08:47.778
[party chatter]

08:47.778 --> 08:50.781
♪

09:05.087 --> 09:07.172
- Sorry to just show up like this.

09:08.173 --> 09:09.466
- Mia...

09:10.092 --> 09:12.177
Oh my god, I can't believe you're here.

09:12.177 --> 09:14.555
[sighs] I've missed you so much.

09:17.182 --> 09:18.183
[sighs]

09:18.809 --> 09:20.769
Look at you! [laughs]

09:20.769 --> 09:22.479
[laughs]

09:22.479 --> 09:24.773
♪

09:24.773 --> 09:28.694
- Is it me or does champagne
just taste better when it's stolen?

09:28.694 --> 09:31.738
- [laughs] It tastes better
when it's a $400 bottle.

09:31.738 --> 09:34.408
- Hm.
[both laugh]

09:34.408 --> 09:36.535
[insects chirping]
[wakes up phone]

09:36.535 --> 09:37.828
- Still nothing from Felix?

09:37.828 --> 09:39.121
[sleeps phone]

09:39.121 --> 09:40.622
- Nope. [sighs]

09:41.415 --> 09:43.250
I think it's really over with us.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.043
- You sad?

09:45.043 --> 09:46.044
- Yeah.

09:46.044 --> 09:47.671
But, not in an Olivia Rodrigo

09:47.671 --> 09:50.507
write-a-whole-album-wishing-
I-could-castrate-him kind of way.

09:50.507 --> 09:51.508
[laughs]

09:52.301 --> 09:54.553
I'm really glad I met Felix.

09:55.429 --> 09:58.807
He helped me stop caring about
what other people think.

10:00.475 --> 10:02.102
Were you sad
when you broke up with Andrew?

10:02.102 --> 10:03.896
- Yes,

10:03.896 --> 10:06.815
but mostly 'cause I left
my favorite hoodie at his house.

10:06.815 --> 10:08.901
But, actually...

10:09.359 --> 10:12.279
Dating him helped me
figure out some stuff, too.

10:12.279 --> 10:14.281
- What kind of stuff?

10:14.281 --> 10:16.533
♪

10:16.533 --> 10:17.534
[door opens]

10:18.076 --> 10:19.203
- Oh, shit. We got to go.

10:19.203 --> 10:21.747
- Oh, uh, your parents?

10:21.747 --> 10:23.665
- Oh my god,
I wish my house was this nice.

10:23.665 --> 10:25.667
- Wait, Lucy, whose house is this?

10:25.667 --> 10:27.711
- I don't know.
There was a for sale sign out front.

10:27.711 --> 10:29.713
I thought it was empty.
- Oh my god.

10:30.339 --> 10:31.924
- We got to go. We got to go!

10:31.924 --> 10:34.927
[both laugh]

10:34.927 --> 10:37.429
MAN:
Somebody there? Hello?

10:37.429 --> 10:39.431
♪ "Silver Velvet" by
The Courtneys playing ♪

10:39.431 --> 10:42.351
♪ The day is getting shady ♪

10:42.351 --> 10:45.521
♪ Playing in the isle ♪

10:45.521 --> 10:48.023
♪ There's nothing
in this life to do ♪

10:48.982 --> 10:51.109
♪ But stay here for a while ♪

10:52.277 --> 10:55.322
♪ The day is getting shady ♪

10:55.322 --> 10:56.782
♪ Playing in the isle... ♪

10:56.782 --> 10:59.660
- You know, my family's going up
to Aspen for the winter break.

11:00.577 --> 11:04.122
Is there any chance
you'd like to come with?

11:04.122 --> 11:05.624
- To Aspen?

11:06.166 --> 11:08.085
I-I don't know how to ski.

11:08.085 --> 11:09.336
- Oh, you'll pick it up.

11:10.087 --> 11:12.214
Or you'll look cute
falling on your butt.

11:12.214 --> 11:13.590
- Oh, okay!

11:13.590 --> 11:16.593
[laughter]

11:18.053 --> 11:19.137
- Now, hold on a sec.

11:19.137 --> 11:20.389
[siren chirps]

11:22.057 --> 11:23.767
- Think there's an accident?

11:24.643 --> 11:26.645
OFFICER:
License and registration, please.

11:26.645 --> 11:27.980
Have anything to drink tonight?

11:27.980 --> 11:29.982
♪

11:29.982 --> 11:31.692
It's a DUI checkpoint.

11:33.026 --> 11:36.029
- Okay, so?
It's not like you've been drinking.

11:38.907 --> 11:39.908
Benji?

11:45.998 --> 11:47.541
♪

11:50.544 --> 11:53.547
♪

11:54.298 --> 11:57.968
- So, before you came over,
I was upset.

11:58.927 --> 12:02.556
Just a few drinks,
and I know I shouldn't have driven,

12:02.556 --> 12:04.600
but my dad was standing right there,
and I just...

12:04.600 --> 12:06.602
I-I didn't know what to do,
you know? So, I...

12:08.437 --> 12:09.479
- Switch with me.

12:10.647 --> 12:12.566
You just got your license back.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.401
Put the car in park
and switch with me, Benji.

12:20.324 --> 12:21.867
[seatbelts clicking]

12:23.619 --> 12:25.621
Nobody saw. Everything's gonna be okay.

12:25.621 --> 12:28.624
[police radio chatter]

12:34.546 --> 12:36.715
[quiet street chatter]

12:36.715 --> 12:39.718
- Carrot cake sans raisin.

12:40.636 --> 12:42.304
Sans cake.

12:42.304 --> 12:44.014
Just frosting.

12:44.473 --> 12:47.100
- That's how I like it. [laughs]
- Mm. Mm.

12:47.809 --> 12:51.271
- Okay, my parents are in the next room.
Could you kiss a little quieter?

12:52.147 --> 12:55.484
- Alternative solution.
Why don't we just tell your parents?

12:56.568 --> 12:58.278
Pilar, they've been really good to me.

12:58.278 --> 13:00.280
They took me in when my mom
was going through all that stuff.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.115
I just-- I don't feel great lying to them.

13:02.115 --> 13:03.909
- After the first few times,
you get used to it.

13:03.909 --> 13:06.453
- Don't you think they'd be happy for us?

13:07.496 --> 13:09.122
- Can we slow down? I mean,

13:09.122 --> 13:12.334
we haven't even gone on a date.
We just kissed.

13:12.334 --> 13:14.169
- Oh, who did you kiss?

13:14.169 --> 13:16.463
- What? No one. Who did you kiss?

13:16.463 --> 13:19.508
- Pilar, come on.
I just heard you say you kissed someone.

13:20.300 --> 13:21.969
Pilar:
I was reading a text.

13:21.969 --> 13:24.513
- Honey! It's okay.

13:24.513 --> 13:27.516
You can tell me if there's
someone special in your life.

13:27.516 --> 13:28.767
♪

13:28.767 --> 13:30.769
- There's nobody. I promise.

13:32.229 --> 13:34.565
- Uh, yeah, I, uh--
You know, I think I should go.

13:34.565 --> 13:37.317
I don't know when,
um, uh, Victor's coming home.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.610
So, that's...

13:38.610 --> 13:40.279
Um...

13:40.279 --> 13:42.489
Yeah, that's-- I mean,
that's the reason why I came here, right?

13:43.866 --> 13:45.784
[door opens, shuts]

13:46.493 --> 13:48.537
- Such a sweet boy.

13:51.123 --> 13:53.083
What the heck happened to my cake?

13:54.084 --> 13:56.253
- [sighs] You don't think that
house had cameras, do you?

13:56.253 --> 13:59.006
- Oh, Lucy, don't even joke.
I can't go to prison for this.

13:59.006 --> 14:01.300
All that overhead lighting.
So unflattering.

14:01.300 --> 14:02.301
[laughs]

14:03.010 --> 14:05.846
- Hey, uh, do you think I could
borrow something to wear?

14:05.846 --> 14:08.765
This uniform smells like shrimp cocktail
and minimum wage.

14:08.765 --> 14:10.893
- [laughs] Yeah, sure. Help yourself.

14:12.978 --> 14:16.356
You know, you never did tell me how you
ended up cater-waitering Harold's wedding.

14:17.024 --> 14:20.110
- I pick up a lot of jobs.
I'm trying to save up as much as I can

14:20.110 --> 14:23.197
so I can get out of here
as soon as humanly possible.

14:23.197 --> 14:25.449
♪

14:29.953 --> 14:31.955
- Um, you don't like Creekwood?

14:32.956 --> 14:34.958
You know, if you're not happy
living in a town

14:34.958 --> 14:37.628
with two Lululemons,
I don't know what to tell you.

14:37.628 --> 14:40.464
- Three. They, uh, just turned
the animal shelter into one.

14:40.464 --> 14:41.590
- Oh!

14:42.174 --> 14:45.010
- I just feel like I'm kinda
stuck here. Like...

14:45.010 --> 14:47.763
I'm waiting for my real life to start.

14:48.514 --> 14:51.183
You probably don't know what that's like.
I mean, high school is always amazing

14:51.183 --> 14:52.434
for the popular, pretty girls.

14:53.852 --> 14:56.063
- Uh, I-I'm okay.

14:56.063 --> 14:58.106
But you are, like, next-level gorge

14:58.106 --> 14:59.399
and way cooler than I am.

14:59.399 --> 15:02.778
Like "Twilight"-era Kristen Stewart,
but capable of smiling.

15:03.695 --> 15:05.197
[giggles]

15:05.197 --> 15:07.616
- Yeah, but you have, like,

15:07.616 --> 15:09.117
the perfect hair,

15:09.117 --> 15:10.536
and the perfect clothes,

15:10.536 --> 15:12.371
and the perfect body.

15:13.622 --> 15:16.124
- Uh, I'm hardly perfect. Um...

15:17.376 --> 15:19.711
My right boob's a tiny bit
smaller than the left.

15:21.088 --> 15:22.589
- Perfect to me.

15:22.589 --> 15:26.051
♪

15:32.558 --> 15:33.600
Um...

15:34.309 --> 15:35.602
I...

15:35.602 --> 15:38.480
thought I heard my phone.

15:38.480 --> 15:40.148
Um...

15:40.148 --> 15:41.650
Still no word from Felix.

15:43.610 --> 15:45.195
- Oh, that's too bad.

15:45.988 --> 15:47.906
You know, it's kind of late. Um...

15:47.906 --> 15:49.867
I think I'm going to go. Uh...

15:49.867 --> 15:51.869
Can I get this back to you another time?

15:51.869 --> 15:53.620
- Yeah. Whenever you want.

15:55.163 --> 15:57.165
- Okay.
- Bye.

16:01.044 --> 16:02.880
[door opens, shuts]

16:02.880 --> 16:05.048
[party chatter, cheering]

16:05.048 --> 16:08.010
NAOMI:
I swear, I woke up this morning,

16:08.010 --> 16:09.553
and I just knew something good
was gonna happen.

16:09.553 --> 16:11.388
The universe brought you here.

16:11.388 --> 16:13.724
- [laughs]
Actually, one of your emails did.

16:13.724 --> 16:16.435
'Cause you mentioned
that you were crashing

16:16.435 --> 16:18.353
with your friend Layla
in Savannah?

16:18.353 --> 16:21.190
[laughs]
- Only since I've been back in the States.

16:21.190 --> 16:23.400
- Oh yeah. You were in Ghana, right?

16:23.400 --> 16:25.861
For a-a sculpture installation?

16:25.861 --> 16:27.446
That's so cool.

16:27.446 --> 16:29.781
- Well, Ghana is a marvel. Have you been?

16:29.781 --> 16:32.868
- Um, not--
- To Ghana?

16:32.868 --> 16:34.620
Oh, she's been meaning to,
and then she remembered

16:34.620 --> 16:35.871
she's in high school.

16:35.871 --> 16:38.248
[nervous laughter]

16:38.248 --> 16:40.250
- Let's not talk about high school.
That's boring.

16:40.250 --> 16:44.129
- I still can't believe you
ended up with Andrew Spencer.

16:44.129 --> 16:46.340
Remember when he used to
chase you around on his scooter?

16:46.340 --> 16:49.134
[laughing]
Oh! And he had the chunkiest cheeks!

16:49.134 --> 16:51.303
Oh, Layla, honey.

16:51.303 --> 16:53.013
Can you get over

16:53.013 --> 16:55.849
how absolutely
breathtaking my daughter is?

16:55.849 --> 16:58.727
- It's good to see you, baby.
Your mom talks about you all the time.

16:59.269 --> 17:00.896
- Uh, guilty.

17:01.772 --> 17:04.733
I'm very, very proud of you.

17:05.651 --> 17:06.985
LAYLA:
There are two guys back there,

17:06.985 --> 17:08.779
and one keeps talking about you--

17:08.779 --> 17:11.490
- [quietly]
But, like, what is she proud of?

17:11.490 --> 17:13.450
She doesn't know anything about you.

17:14.576 --> 17:16.203
- Wait, wait. No, I know things.

17:16.203 --> 17:18.413
♪ party music continues ♪

17:18.413 --> 17:21.708
I-I get bits and pieces
from your dad's posts,

17:21.708 --> 17:23.418
like your sophomore art show.

17:23.418 --> 17:26.755
Those lightbox portraits.
They were gallery-ready. Hm.

17:27.464 --> 17:30.092
I just... I wish I could have
seen them in the flesh.

17:30.092 --> 17:32.636
- I mean, you could have.
It was a high school art show.

17:32.636 --> 17:34.221
I can't imagine tickets
were very hard to come by.

17:34.221 --> 17:36.765
- Andrew, it's fine. It's fine.

17:37.808 --> 17:38.851
It's fine.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.562
- I should have been there.

17:42.187 --> 17:43.313
And I wasn't.

17:47.025 --> 17:48.277
Uh...

17:49.611 --> 17:51.113
Could you, uh, excuse me for a moment?

17:51.113 --> 17:53.490
♪

17:57.494 --> 17:58.996
- What the hell was that?

18:00.706 --> 18:02.207
[sighs]

18:02.207 --> 18:03.625
VICTOR:
Benji...

18:03.625 --> 18:06.962
Look, it's okay. They waved us
right through the checkpoint.

18:06.962 --> 18:09.923
- But what if they saw us switching seats?

18:10.924 --> 18:13.302
I don't understand how you're
being so nice about this.

18:15.012 --> 18:16.180
- Because...

18:16.180 --> 18:17.806
I love you.

18:19.474 --> 18:21.476
You drank. You slipped up.

18:23.020 --> 18:25.647
But, you'll call your sponsor tomorrow,

18:25.647 --> 18:27.649
and, and you'll start over.

18:32.779 --> 18:34.072
- Hey, guys. Sorry to interrupt.

18:34.072 --> 18:37.159
I just have an early morning,
so I want to get my keys back before bed.

18:37.743 --> 18:40.787
♪

18:46.126 --> 18:47.503
[keys jingling]

18:49.171 --> 18:50.631
Why does Victor have my keys?

18:51.507 --> 18:53.050
- Uh...

18:53.050 --> 18:55.928
I-I never drove a Range Rover before,

18:55.928 --> 18:58.555
so Benji let me drive it
for the last few blocks.

18:59.806 --> 19:00.891
- Pretty sweet ride, right?

19:00.891 --> 19:02.643
- [laughs] Yeah.

19:03.185 --> 19:04.978
- Good night, guys.
VICTOR: Good night.

19:06.563 --> 19:09.024
- Wait. Dad.

19:11.693 --> 19:13.195
[sighs] I can't do this.

19:15.531 --> 19:17.074
- What is it, Benji?

19:17.783 --> 19:19.493
- I have to tell my parents.

19:21.161 --> 19:22.663
I think you should go.

19:24.581 --> 19:26.124
♪

19:34.508 --> 19:36.260
- Hey, man. What are you doing?

19:36.260 --> 19:38.136
- Hey! Waiting for you to get home.

19:38.136 --> 19:39.972
- And annoying Mrs. Loo in 202?

19:40.973 --> 19:44.101
Sorry. Things with Benji went
a little longer than expected.

19:44.101 --> 19:46.478
- Yeah, they did.
- [laughs] No, not...

19:47.396 --> 19:48.480
Not like that.

19:50.023 --> 19:51.024
Benji's...

19:52.568 --> 19:55.863
He's going through some, uh,
pretty intense personal stuff

19:55.863 --> 19:57.531
that I can't really talk about right now.

19:59.449 --> 20:00.492
- Okay.

20:02.035 --> 20:04.329
- But, uh, [sighs] what about you?

20:04.329 --> 20:06.081
Did you end up getting with my sister?

20:08.083 --> 20:11.128
I tried to sound supportive.
[laughs]

20:11.128 --> 20:13.505
- No, it's fine. Not yet. You know...

20:14.173 --> 20:16.675
Everything with Pilar was great, but...

20:17.676 --> 20:19.845
she got weird about your parents knowing.

20:21.471 --> 20:22.848
- Hm.

20:23.640 --> 20:25.142
- That was an ominous "hm."

20:26.810 --> 20:28.437
Do your parents not like me?

20:28.437 --> 20:30.355
Is my Salazar family crush unrequited?

20:30.355 --> 20:32.608
- [laughs] No. My family loves you.

20:32.608 --> 20:36.278
It-it's just that if they find out
that you're seeing Pilar, they might...

20:37.154 --> 20:38.238
love you less.

20:38.238 --> 20:39.698
- What? Why?

20:40.991 --> 20:43.243
- Well, they're very protective over her.

20:43.243 --> 20:45.120
Like. when she had
a boyfriend back in Texas,

20:45.120 --> 20:47.122
my dad took her door off her bedroom.

20:48.707 --> 20:50.000
- Okay, that is a little bit psycho.

20:50.834 --> 20:53.629
- Listen, man, Latino dads
and their daughters, it's a real thing.

20:54.379 --> 20:55.756
So,

20:55.756 --> 20:58.091
maybe just let Pilar lead
the way on this one for a little while.

21:00.302 --> 21:02.012
- Okay.
- Yeah.

21:02.012 --> 21:03.889
- Hey, and whatever mystery thing's
going on with Benji,

21:03.889 --> 21:05.098
you guys are gonna get through it.

21:05.098 --> 21:07.226
If you're half as good at kissing
as your sister--

21:07.226 --> 21:09.603
- Dude!
- I regretted that as soon as I said it.

21:09.603 --> 21:12.606
[party chatter, cheering]

21:12.606 --> 21:15.609
♪ "Shining All Night"
by Alex Nova playing ♪

21:17.277 --> 21:18.570
♪ I don't need the... ♪

21:18.570 --> 21:20.572
[door shuts, music muffled]
MIA: Hey.

21:21.406 --> 21:23.909
Um, sorry about Andrew.

21:23.909 --> 21:24.952
- Oh, I get it.

21:24.952 --> 21:27.663
I'd be wary of me, too.

21:29.706 --> 21:32.584
- Um... So, my dad got remarried today.

21:33.794 --> 21:36.922
- And how do we feel about her?

21:37.548 --> 21:38.674
Veronica, right?

21:39.383 --> 21:41.426
- It took a minute,

21:41.426 --> 21:43.428
uh, but she's actually pretty great.

21:45.097 --> 21:47.558
It's my dad who I'm struggling
with right now.

21:48.392 --> 21:50.394
He just got offered a new job.

21:50.394 --> 21:52.855
He wants to move us across the country,

21:52.855 --> 21:56.400
and he doesn't care at all what I want.

21:58.360 --> 21:59.695
- Sounds familiar.

22:02.823 --> 22:03.824
[sighs]

22:05.492 --> 22:07.494
- Is that why you left?

22:08.495 --> 22:10.497
I've only ever heard his side.

22:12.249 --> 22:13.959
- When you were 4 or 5,

22:13.959 --> 22:17.171
I got an offer to show
in this tiny gallery in Paris.

22:18.172 --> 22:20.382
Nothing prestigious, but...

22:20.382 --> 22:21.800
it meant something to me.

22:21.800 --> 22:25.846
I'll never forget the look on his face
when I said I wanted us to go to Paris.

22:26.430 --> 22:29.892
Like I was a stupid child,
living in a dream world.

22:30.601 --> 22:32.811
- So, that's why you left?

22:33.854 --> 22:36.773
Because he wouldn't go to Paris with you?

22:36.773 --> 22:38.775
- No, no, of course not.

22:38.775 --> 22:41.153
♪

22:41.153 --> 22:43.155
Don't you understand?

22:43.697 --> 22:45.991
I was losing myself in that house.

22:45.991 --> 22:47.492
- What about me?

22:48.827 --> 22:51.038
- I-I don't know what to say.

22:53.916 --> 22:55.417
It was selfish.

22:56.335 --> 22:58.670
And horrible.

22:58.670 --> 23:01.173
And the worst thing I've ever done.

23:02.925 --> 23:04.426
But...

23:04.426 --> 23:06.595
I am not the person I was when I left.

23:07.221 --> 23:10.432
And I would do anything
to have you in my life again, so...

23:11.266 --> 23:13.310
tell me what I can do.

23:15.854 --> 23:17.648
- You could move to Creekwood.

23:17.648 --> 23:20.567
- What?
- You could move to Creekwood.

23:21.318 --> 23:23.946
I mean, if you were there,
then I wouldn't have to move.

23:25.781 --> 23:28.158
- Oh.
- And we could...

23:28.158 --> 23:30.244
maybe work on our relationship.

23:30.244 --> 23:33.121
And maybe, um...

23:34.456 --> 23:36.792
I don't know. Try to...

23:36.792 --> 23:38.627
heal? [laughs]

23:40.128 --> 23:41.129
[sighs]

23:42.673 --> 23:44.299
- I love that idea.

23:46.009 --> 23:48.720
But I'm supposed to go to Prague
in a few weeks.

23:48.720 --> 23:51.181
I accepted a residency at a gallery there.

23:51.181 --> 23:52.182
♪

23:52.182 --> 23:54.643
But, it's only for a few months.

23:55.894 --> 23:57.855
So, maybe after that?

23:57.855 --> 24:00.524
I-I think after that would work great.

24:02.317 --> 24:04.403
- This was a mistake.

24:06.780 --> 24:08.115
- Mia.

24:10.117 --> 24:12.578
- I don't know why I thought
it would be different.

24:12.578 --> 24:14.079
Can you take me home?

24:14.997 --> 24:16.498
- Okay.

24:16.498 --> 24:18.333
♪

24:18.333 --> 24:21.003
♪ Oh... ♪

24:23.589 --> 24:26.967
♪ Oh, oh... ♪

24:28.719 --> 24:30.637
♪ Oh... ♪

24:33.807 --> 24:36.101
♪ Oh, oh... ♪

24:38.979 --> 24:40.606
♪ Oh... ♪

24:44.151 --> 24:47.613
♪ Oh, oh... ♪

24:49.281 --> 24:50.741
♪ Oh... ♪

24:52.659 --> 24:55.329
[praying in Arabic]

24:55.829 --> 24:57.748
[repeats prayer]

24:58.957 --> 25:01.043
[repeats prayer]

25:02.669 --> 25:05.380
[repeats prayer]

25:08.383 --> 25:09.885
♪ "chance with you"
by mehro playing ♪

25:09.885 --> 25:12.471
♪ Oh, I've heard all about you ♪

25:12.471 --> 25:15.766
♪ All those things they had to say ♪

25:15.766 --> 25:19.102
♪ You're a legend 'round this school ♪

25:19.102 --> 25:22.356
♪ Locally famous drama queen ♪

25:22.356 --> 25:25.692
♪ Turn my eyes, I see you stare ♪

25:25.692 --> 25:29.071
♪ 'Cross the room and right at me ♪

25:29.071 --> 25:32.449
♪ Now, you're smiling like you've got ♪

25:32.449 --> 25:35.827
♪ Like you've got something on your mind ♪

25:35.827 --> 25:38.622
♪ You're so beautiful ♪

25:38.622 --> 25:42.376
♪ I don't want to turn away ♪

25:42.376 --> 25:45.087
♪ You've been here before ♪

25:45.087 --> 25:45.796
[sends text]

25:45.796 --> 25:49.049
♪ Make me feel like you're a... ♪

25:49.466 --> 25:53.178
♪ If I could go back in time ♪

25:55.305 --> 25:57.641
♪ I'd shoot my shot ♪

25:57.641 --> 25:58.308
[sends text]

25:59.059 --> 26:02.479
♪ Just so I could have a chance ♪

26:02.479 --> 26:05.357
♪ With you... ♪

26:09.778 --> 26:10.988
SHIRIN:
Morning.

26:10.988 --> 26:13.490
I saw your tasbih on your dresser.

26:13.490 --> 26:15.576
Was somebody praying last night?

26:15.576 --> 26:17.870
- Yes, Maman. But...

26:19.204 --> 26:21.331
I don't think it worked.

26:21.331 --> 26:23.750
Pretty sure you're not supposed
to pray for a boy to show up.

26:23.750 --> 26:26.336
Isn't that, like, a big Muslim no-no?

26:28.922 --> 26:30.007
- When I was pregnant,

26:30.007 --> 26:32.467
I prayed every day for a boy to show up,

26:32.467 --> 26:36.013
and God delivered
the greatest gift of my life.

26:36.013 --> 26:37.306
Your brother Nasser.

26:37.973 --> 26:39.099
- Okay.

26:40.809 --> 26:42.519
- Rahim.

26:42.519 --> 26:44.646
I know it may not
feel this way right now,

26:44.646 --> 26:47.149
but I believe God has a plan for you.

26:47.149 --> 26:50.110
And that plan includes
someone who will love you

26:50.110 --> 26:51.653
with all his heart.

26:51.653 --> 26:53.363
So, it is written.

26:53.363 --> 26:55.199
♪

26:55.199 --> 26:56.700
- It is written.

26:57.201 --> 26:57.951
[doorbell rings]

26:58.785 --> 27:00.370
- It's open!

27:01.997 --> 27:05.167
Lucy! Long time no see.

27:05.751 --> 27:07.336
- I just wanted to give you this.

27:07.336 --> 27:09.213
- Oh.
- I washed it.

27:09.213 --> 27:12.007
Actually, I didn't,
but I did spritz it with Febreze.

27:13.175 --> 27:15.219
- Right. Okay, well, you...

27:15.219 --> 27:18.096
didn't have to do that, but thanks.

27:22.851 --> 27:24.978
I had a lot of fun last night. Um...

27:24.978 --> 27:28.440
Sorry if I kind of killed
the vibe at the end.

27:28.440 --> 27:29.733
- We don't have to talk about.

27:29.733 --> 27:31.235
- No, no, I want to. Um...

27:32.945 --> 27:34.571
I think I just got scared.

27:36.698 --> 27:39.660
Not because I didn't want it
to happen, but...

27:41.370 --> 27:42.704
because I did.

27:44.373 --> 27:45.415
- Oh.

27:46.458 --> 27:48.460
- Yeah. Oh.

27:48.460 --> 27:51.463
♪ "Treat Me Like Fire"
by Lion Babe playing ♪

27:52.548 --> 27:54.550
- So, what now?

28:03.433 --> 28:04.768
♪ Treat me like ♪

28:04.768 --> 28:06.144
♪ Treat me like ♪

28:06.144 --> 28:07.354
♪ Treat me like ♪

28:07.354 --> 28:09.189
♪ Treat me like... fire ♪

28:09.189 --> 28:11.358
Holy shit.
[laughs]

28:11.358 --> 28:13.569
♪ Fire, fire ♪

28:13.569 --> 28:16.196
♪ Into the pain, into the pain ♪

28:16.196 --> 28:17.447
♪ Into the pain ♪

28:17.447 --> 28:18.907
♪ Into the pain... ♪

28:20.325 --> 28:21.660
[knocking]

28:23.871 --> 28:26.290
- Hey. Hey, don't worry.
I told your parents

28:26.290 --> 28:28.709
that I was helping
your dad move back in today,

28:28.709 --> 28:32.087
so now I get to lug
heavy boxes up the stairs.

28:33.297 --> 28:35.340
- Hey, I'm sorry about last night.

28:36.675 --> 28:38.343
- There's nothing--
There's nothing to be sorry about.

28:39.344 --> 28:41.263
I ended up talking to Victor.

28:42.639 --> 28:45.100
Why didn't you tell me
your dad's protective of you?

28:45.100 --> 28:47.019
- Because it's humiliating.

28:47.978 --> 28:49.646
I mean, the whole time I've known you,

28:49.646 --> 28:51.440
I've been Victor's baby sister,

28:51.440 --> 28:54.151
and I didn't want you to see me
as some little girl

28:54.151 --> 28:55.986
whose dad watches over her like a hawk.

28:55.986 --> 28:57.613
- I don't see that way.

28:58.071 --> 29:01.283
Okay, I see you as a super-smart,

29:01.283 --> 29:04.286
bad-ass, model-gorgeous neighbor

29:04.286 --> 29:06.163
whose father would murder me

29:06.163 --> 29:08.665
if he knew the thoughts running
through my head right now.

29:08.665 --> 29:11.627
♪

29:14.213 --> 29:15.672
- What kind of thoughts?

29:16.215 --> 29:17.549
- Trust me, we're not there yet.

29:17.549 --> 29:20.844
♪ Ooh ooh... ♪

29:22.387 --> 29:26.058
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh... ♪

29:27.184 --> 29:29.937
♪ Ooh ooh... ♪

29:29.937 --> 29:31.480
♪ Oh oh... ♪

29:31.939 --> 29:35.317
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh... ♪

29:36.693 --> 29:38.362
- Sweetheart.

29:39.279 --> 29:41.240
Thank God. I was, uh,

29:41.240 --> 29:42.741
I was worried about you.

29:44.326 --> 29:46.161
Listen, um...

29:47.996 --> 29:50.999
I handled things terribly.
I should have been able--

29:52.501 --> 29:53.502
♪ Oh ♪

29:54.545 --> 29:55.546
♪ Ooh ♪

29:56.046 --> 29:59.049
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh... ♪

30:00.717 --> 30:03.554
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh... ♪

30:04.888 --> 30:06.640
We are going to figure this out.

30:06.640 --> 30:08.141
Okay?

30:10.769 --> 30:13.814
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh... ♪

30:13.814 --> 30:16.525
[birds chirping]

30:16.525 --> 30:17.776
- You, uh,

30:18.819 --> 30:21.738
weren't responding to my texts,
so I just-- I got worried.

30:21.738 --> 30:23.740
- Well, my parents took my phone away.

30:25.033 --> 30:27.452
- Do we need to get you a burner?
L-like in the spy movies?

30:27.452 --> 30:29.872
We could hide it under a floorboard.

30:30.539 --> 30:31.790
- Victor, I'm...

30:33.500 --> 30:34.710
I'm going to rehab.

30:35.836 --> 30:36.879
- What?

30:37.504 --> 30:39.214
- Yeah, my...

30:39.214 --> 30:42.301
My dad set it up this morning.
It's an in-patient program.

30:42.301 --> 30:45.345
- Wait, rehab?
This is crazy.

30:46.847 --> 30:48.348
- Actually, it's...

30:49.266 --> 30:51.727
It's not.
- You had a slipup. You drank one time

30:51.727 --> 30:53.770
in a year.
- It wasn't just one time.

30:53.770 --> 30:55.522
♪

30:55.522 --> 30:58.233
I've been drinking sometimes.

31:00.736 --> 31:01.862
- When?

31:03.780 --> 31:05.282
- Before a big test.

31:06.158 --> 31:07.868
After a fight with my parents.

31:08.785 --> 31:11.413
The night I came over your house
and yelled at your mom.

31:12.080 --> 31:14.499
Look, I've been running away from it,
just wanting it to go away,

31:14.499 --> 31:16.919
but it-it won't.
And then, last night,

31:17.920 --> 31:19.546
I lied to you.

31:19.546 --> 31:21.840
I drove. I put you in danger.

31:21.840 --> 31:23.592
Look, Victor, if you and I are gonna have

31:23.592 --> 31:26.595
any real chance of working out,
then I have to figure this out.

31:27.095 --> 31:28.597
And I have to do it alone.

31:29.640 --> 31:32.267
Okay? So, that means three weeks,
no emails, no phone.

31:34.561 --> 31:37.147
I think it's going to be
really good for me.

31:37.147 --> 31:38.941
